@startuml
' Author: Nicholas Irvine  GitHub https://github.com/SaladStik  LinkedIn https://www.linkedin.com/in/nicholas-irvine-303ab5284/
title Orbit CI to GitOps

' Code push and deploy connect through git. CI builds the
' image. Image Updater writes the new tag back to git. Argo CD does the deploy.

actor Developer
participant "GitHub Actions\n(build-changed-service)" as ci
participant "GHCR\nghcr.io/<owner>/orbit-<svc>" as ghcr
participant "Argo CD\nImage Updater" as updater
participant "Git repo" as git
participant "Argo CD\n(sync)" as argo
participant "Kubernetes\nDeployment" as k8s

Developer -> git : git push (services/**)
git -> ci : trigger workflow
ci -> ci : detect CHANGED service\n(path filters)
ci -> ci : build ONLY that service
ci -> ghcr : push image\ntag = commit SHA

updater -> ghcr : poll for new SHA tags
ghcr --> updater : new tag found
updater -> git : commit new tag\nback into manifests

git -> argo : desired state changed
argo -> k8s : sync -> rolling update
k8s --> argo : new pods healthy

note over git : Git is the source of truth. Even the tag bump is a commit. CI never touches the cluster.

@enduml
